Key Match Events: Tomáš Suslov scored the winning goal for Slovakia in the 70th minute
Karl Jakob Hein made strong saves from Hellas Verone midfielder Tomaš Suslov and Union Berlin's László Bénes
Pre-Game Insights: Estonia started the game with the intent to play on the front foot
Estonia knew Slovakia were a good team, they play good football, run behind the line with several players and are dangerous all the time
Post-Match Reflections: Estonian head coach Jürgen Henn admitted he was pretty disappointed with the result
Karl Jakob Hein said the team was good, but they had to be resilient and defend well against Slovakia's pressure
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Tallinn's A. Le Coq Arena in front of a crowd of over 6,000 fans
Estonia will face Sweden away on Sunday
The match will be shown live on ETV+ here with coverage beginning at 9.30 p.m.
Others: Sweden beat Azerbaijan 3-1 in Baku thanks to two goals from Newcastle United's Alexander Isak and a penalty from Viktor Gyökers of Sporting CP
